{
  "stem": "24195.6",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave us-- every day, they entertained us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They put us up in, in first class hotels, gave us pocket-- you know, expense money every day to spend, you know?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were just treated as royalty-- wonderful program.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were the youngest couple on that, on that flight.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a charter flight from New York directly to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And these people were all old.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, they were all-- I was then, what, 40 years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, my wife was in her 30s.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were youngest.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were people in the 60s, 70s, and 80s, somewhere and, you know, only walking around with a cane.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because they, they had been here for a long time in the US, or in-- and they were just-- you know, it was just the-- I, I don't think-- they went by age, really.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The only reason I got on this early in 1971 was because the, the press attache in the New York office, in the New York German embassy, was a former colleague of mine at that newspaper.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He worked on that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were, we were friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- when I found out that he was stationed in New York and we got together, he says, why don't you-- don't you want to go back to Berlin?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a free trip, you know, and everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You get the royal treatment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he put me on the-- he had the, he had the authority to put it on the list.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So and so then I worked, you know, with the ADA for 20 years.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In 19-- For the ADA, the American Dental Association?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, the American Dental Association-- then in 1981, I left them for Hill and Knowlton, one of the major public relations-- US public relations firms.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
